    "framing": "Set-ConCA achieves 64.5% +/- 5.0pp cross-family transfer from Gemma-3 4B -> LLaMA-3 8B. Crucially, transferring from the larger model to the smaller model (LLaMA-3 8B -> Gemma-3 4B) achieves 55.2% +/- 1.7pp. The fact that bi-directional transfer works equally well supports the Platonic Representation Hypothesis: both models share an underlying semantic geometry, and one is not simply a subset of the other."
  },
