    "framing": "Pure Gemma-3 intra-family transfer (Gemma-3 4B -> Gemma-3 1B) achieves ~55.7%, and transferring smaller to bigger (1B -> 4B) achieves ~55.2%. Both are lower than the cross-family 64.6% result (Gemma-3 4B <-> LLaMA-3 8B). This confirms that the alignment issue is not just about moving between different recipes (like Gemma-2 9B), but relates fundamentally to model capacity and feature resolution. Gemma-3 1B is highly capacity-constrained and likely combines or drops features that Gemma-3 4B and LLaMA-3 8B independently resolve. Thus, two large models from different families (4B/8B) share MORE conceptual structure with each other than a large model shares with its smaller 1B sibling."
  },
