    "framing": "The correct comparison is among SPARSE + INTERPRETABLE methods: Set-ConCA, SAE-L1, and SAE-TopK. PCA and PCA-Threshold are non-sparse (L0\u22481.0) and non-interpretable \u2014 they are included as reconstruction upper bounds only. Among sparse methods, Set-ConCA achieves lower MSE than both SAE variants at equivalent sparsity (L0=25%), while also delivering superior cross-model transfer (EXP4). SAE-TopK is the fairest apples-to-apples comparison: same sparsity constraint (exactly k=32 active), pointwise architecture. Set-ConCA beats SAE-TopK on MSE and substantially on transfer overlap (+14.7pp)."
  },
